The Herald Court Reporter
THE trial of Harare lawyer Everson Samukange and his former secretary, Theresa Machawira, who are facing extortion, money laundering and fraud charges involving US$294 031 resumed on Tuesday with the pair applying for exception to the charges. Samukange and Machawira, through their legal counsel, advocates Fadzai Mahere and Taona Nyamakura,   instructed by Harrison Nkomo, are alleged to have committed the offences when they were employed at Venturas and Samukange Law Firm. Samukange and Machawira told magistrate Mr Francis Mapfumo that the allegations do not carry essential elements that forms the charges. Prosecutor Michael Reza is expected to respond today with magistrate Mapfumo expected to make a ruling on July 3.